  "text": "## Kafka ProduceRequest Network Write Chain\n\nThis traces the flow of a Kafka ProduceRequest from the KafkaProducer.send() call to the broker's log append in apache/kafka.\n\n### Producer Side (Client)\n\n1. **KafkaProducer.send()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java, lines 941-945)\n   - Public API method that accepts a ProducerRecord and optional callback\n   - Intercepts the record and delegates to doSend()\n\n2. **RecordAccumulator.append()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java, lines 275+)\n   - Called from KafkaProducer.doSend()\n   - Accumulates records into MemoryRecords batches\n   - Returns a RecordAppendResult indicating whether the batch is ready to send\n\n3. **Sender.sendProducerData()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java, lines 357-443)\n   - Background thread that continuously processes accumulated records\n   - Calls accumulator.ready() and accumulator.drain() to get batches ready for sending\n   - Calls sendProduceRequests() to convert batches into ProduceRequest instances\n\n4. **Sender.sendProduceRequest()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java, lines 864-915)\n   - Creates a ProduceRequest with ProduceRequestData\n   - Constructs a ClientRequest via client.newClientRequest()\n   - Calls client.send(clientRequest, now)\n\n### Network Layer\n\n5. **NetworkClient.send()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java, lines 541-543)\n   - Public KafkaClient interface implementation\n   - Delegates to doSend(ClientRequest, isInternalRequest, now)\n   - Eventually calls selector.send() with NetworkSend to transmit data over the network\n\n### Broker Side (Server)\n\n6. **KafkaApis.handleProduceRequest()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala, lines 388-550)\n   - Processes incoming ProduceRequest on the broker\n   - Performs authorization checks and validation\n   - Calls replicaManager.handleProduceAppend() at line 535 to append records to the log\n\n7. **ReplicaManager.handleProduceAppend()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala, lines 731-760)\n   - Wrapper method that handles transactional verification\n   - Calls appendRecords() to perform the actual append\n\n8. **ReplicaManager.appendRecords()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala, lines 674-712)\n   - Core method that appends records to the leader replica\n   - Calls appendRecordsToLeader() to write to the log\n   - Handles delayed produce requests via maybeAddDelayedProduce()\n   - Invokes the responseCallback to send the response back to the client\n\n### Summary Flow\nKafkaProducer.send() → RecordAccumulator.append() → Sender.sendProducerData() → Sender.sendProduceRequest() → NetworkClient.send() → [Network] → KafkaApis.handleProduceRequest() → ReplicaManager.handleProduceAppend() → ReplicaManager.appendRecords()\n"
}

